content: SAT philosophy breakthrough: 'All questions easier than you think. Not testing complex math but reasoning ability.' Student realizes 1480 (780 reading/700 math) imbalance hurts CS applications. One silly mistake costs 20-30 points. Rushing through end creates cascade failures.

Immediate pivot strategy: Student requests SAT focus with test next weekend. Jenny: 'Quick 10-min check-in, then 50 minutes SAT.' Maintains project continuity while addressing urgent need. CS application context: 'They really care about math scores.'

Keyword trigger method deployed: 'When see linear, think slope immediately.' Process of elimination: 'If XY=3, one must be 1, other must be 3.' Annotation strategy: 'Start annotating math like reading section.' Concept before shortcut protocol ensures deep understanding.

Jenny shares time constraints: 'I have to hop off, have another thing.' Offers continued support: 'Text me and I'll send explanation with annotated drawing.' Humanizes relationship through shared limitations while maintaining commitment.

Teaching method switch mid-problem: Shows long method first for understanding, student requests shorter way, immediately pivots. 'I wanted you to understand concept before going to shorter one.' Calibrates explanation depth to student preference.

Verbal processing technique framework: 'Explain this problem to me in your words.' Works through understanding gaps, improves retention. Assumption elimination rule: 'Never assume, always use given information.' Prevents exponential vs linear confusion.

Session outcomes: 6+ SAT problems reviewed systematically, rushing pattern identified and addressed, annotation strategy adopted from reading, Folklift 3 interviews secured, Empowering AI toolkit complete, game dialog system working.

Multi-channel execution: Screen annotation during problems, website demo for Folklift, slides review for Empowering AI, text follow-up promised. Seamless transitions between content types maintains engagement across platforms.

Confidence differential technique: 'Your reading section really good, no need to worry. Some people have bad reading, they need worry, not you.' Leverages strength to address weakness. Validates test difficulty: 'I know test really long.'

Simplification principle crystallized: 'Whenever feel doing too much work, you probably are.' All SAT information purposeful: 'They wouldn't give u+t=5 if didn't want you use it.' Transforms test from computation challenge to reasoning puzzle.
